## FAQ

### Can I use React? Vue? That new framework that came out yesterday?

Often, yes - Vibecodr is built to support common browser frameworks and libraries. If a dependency fails to load in the runtime, treat it as an environment constraint and adjust (or remix into a simpler approach), then submit a request for expansion and most likely I will get it done. 

### Where does my vibe run?

In the browser, in an isolated/sandboxed runtime. The point is that other people can run your vibe instantly without you running a server.

### Can my vibe keep secrets?

No. If it is in client-side code, it is not a secret. If you need credentials, use a server-side pulse and keep the client as a public artifact.

### Is Vibecodr open source?

Not by default. This repo does not include an open source license file, so you should assume "all rights reserved" unless that changes.

### Can I self-host Vibecodr?

The production system is Cloudflare-specific and this repo is not intended as a one-command self-host. If self-hosting matters to you, treat Vibecodr as an inspiration/reference, not a turnkey product.

### Is Vibecodr "done"?

No. Vibecodr is in active development. Expect iteration.

